ature of 12K will occur or an unreasonably high fraction of the planet\nwill need to be covered by solar collectors by about 2400 to keep pace with our\ngrowth in energy use. We further discuss the implications in terms of\ninterstellar expansion, the transition to type II and III civilizations, SETI,\nand the Fermi Paradox. We conclude that the \"sustainability solution\" to the\nFermi Paradox is a compelling possibility.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Jun 2018 01:28:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-12"}
