 at least partly explain the observed positive correlation\nbetween stellar metallicity and hJ occurrence. Combined with the observed hJ\noccurrence rate, our results for the survival rate imply that <8 % (alpha =\n1e-3) to <43 % (alpha = 1e-1) of sun-like stars initially encounter an inward\nmigrating hJ. This reconciles models and observations of young spinning stars\nwith the observed hJ pile up and hJ occurrence rates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Jun 2018 11:27:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 8 Apr 2019 09:24:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 4 Jul 2019 08:33:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-07"}
