 an anti-correlation has been\nobserved in samples of stars. Hence the process causing it must be intrinsic to\nthe accretion process, and we speculate that the stellar magnetic field\nconfiguration on the visibile hemisphere affects both the accretion rate and\nthe coronal emission, eventually causing the observed anti-correlation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Jun 2018 15:51:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-17"}
